=Description=

"Follow up to the May 2011 lecture sponsored by NoBAWC (Network of Bay Area Worker Cooperatives) and held at The Women’s Building in San Francisco’s Mission District. Attorney Jenny Kassan of Cutting Edge Capital, The Sustainable Economies Law Center and Katovich Law Group, follows up on audience questions from her discussion of the in and out’s of securities regulation, state and federal law, exemptions, as well as various strategies that small businesses and cooperatives have used to raise needed capital."
